<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,1399,1610,2027]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman" box="[189,473,1610,1637]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref265860" refString="Hayman R. W., Misonne X. &amp; Verheyen W. N. 1966. The bats of the Congo and of Rwanda and Burundi. Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum voor Midden Afrika, Zoologische Wetenschappen, Ser. 8, 154: 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1966">
Hayman 
<emphasis box="[294,352,1611,1637]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al.</emphasis>
(1966: 61
</bibRefCitation>
, map 93) reported this species from the Garamba National Park and Faradje and Aba (Haut-Uélé Province). Additional specimens were found in Rwindi (Nord-Kivu Province), Tandala (Sud-Ubangi Province) and Mbandaka (Equateur Province). All of these localities are in the northern half of the 
<collectingCountry box="[317,380,1717,1743]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">DRC</collectingCountry>
, with the latter two on the western side. These additional records are not mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Happold" box="[189,451,1752,1779]" firstAuthor="Happold" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="516 - 518" refId="ref263572" refString="Happold M. 2013 s. Tadarida major Lappet-eared Free-tailed Bat. In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 516 - 518. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="s">Happold (2013s: 517)</bibRefCitation>
, who mapped the species from a number of distinct areas: one starting from the Garamba National Park along the 
<collectingRegion box="[594,719,1788,1814]" country="Sudan" name="Nahr an Nil" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">River Nile</collectingRegion>
up to Abu Hamad in 
<collectingCountry box="[977,1053,1788,1814]" name="Sudan" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Sudan</collectingCountry>
, a second on the eastern side of Lake Victoria, a third along the coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[690,767,1824,1850]" name="Kenya" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Kenya</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[822,931,1823,1849]" name="Tanzania" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, and finally a larger area in West Africa, starting in eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[401,486,1859,1885]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Guinea</collectingCountry>
and reaching the western part of 
<collectingCountry box="[869,961,1859,1885]" name="Nigeria" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
. Based on the material in 
<bibRefCitation author="ACR" firstAuthor="ACR" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refId="ref254905" refString="ACR. 2016. African Chiroptera Report. AfricanBats, Pretoria. Available from http: // www. africanbats. org / index. php / publications / africa-chiroptera-report [accessed 28 Sep. 2017]." type="url" year="2016">ACR (2016: 1131)</bibRefCitation>
and the climatological data, we believe the species can occur further to the west (to 
<collectingCountry box="[1246,1341,1894,1921]" name="Senegal" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Senegal</collectingCountry>
) and to the east (in western 
<collectingCountry box="[453,558,1930,1957]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
). Additionally 
<bibRefCitation author="ACR" box="[729,947,1930,1956]" firstAuthor="ACR" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refId="ref254905" refString="ACR. 2016. African Chiroptera Report. AfricanBats, Pretoria. Available from http: // www. africanbats. org / index. php / publications / africa-chiroptera-report [accessed 28 Sep. 2017]." type="url" year="2016">ACR (2016: 1131)</bibRefCitation>
refers to material from 
<collectingCountry box="[1227,1349,1930,1956]" name="Cameroon" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
and the 
<collectingCountry box="[232,529,1965,1991]" name="Central African Republic" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Central African Republic</collectingCountry>
, bridging the gap between 
<geoCoordinate box="[842,908,1965,1992]" degrees="10" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" precision="55555" value="10.0">10° E</geoCoordinate>
and 
<geoCoordinate box="[964,1030,1965,1992]" degrees="33" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" precision="55555" value="33.0">33° E</geoCoordinate>
referred to by 
<bibRefCitation author="Happold" firstAuthor="Happold" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="516 - 518" refId="ref263572" refString="Happold M. 2013 s. Tadarida major Lappet-eared Free-tailed Bat. In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 516 - 518. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="s">Happold (2013s: 517)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
